{"000-section": {"000-title": "3 Months Advance Pension to Old Age / Widow / Disabled to Tackle Coronavirus (COVID-19)"}, "001-section": {"000-title": "Central govt. to give 3 months advance pension to old age / widow / disabled pension scheme beneficiaries to tackle Coronavirus (COVID-19) pandemic, senior citizens, vidhwa, viklang to get amount in 1st week of April 2020 in their bank accounts through DBT mode"}, "002-section": {"000-title": "3 Months Advance Pension to Senior Citizens / Vidhwa / Viklang", "001-normal": "After the announcement of 21 day lockdown over Novel Coronavirus (COVID 19), govt. will now provide 3 months pension in advance to old age / widow / disabled beneficiaries. The senior citizens, widow and persons with disabilities can utilize this amount while staying at home. Govt. wants to ensure that there is no shortage of cash, food items, ration, vegetables during curfew in the country. Moreover, the people who are most susceptible to this diseases must stay at home and come out victorious after lockdown is over.", "002-normal": "Under the National Social Assistance Program (NSAP), central govt. provides monthly pension to the poor senior citizens, widows and differently abled. NSAP programme comes under the Ministry of Rural Development of Indian government. There are around 2.98 crore beneficiaries who receives pension every month. The pension amount are transferred into beneficiary bank accounts through DBT mode.", "003-normal": "The centre has now decided to give three months pension in advance to all the 2.98-crore beneficiaries by the first week of April 2020. Now let\u2019s check the amount which would be given to beneficiaries:-", "004-listElement": "- **Senior Citizens (Old Age Pension)** \u2013 As per the NSAP, each elderly citizen in the age group of 60 to 79 years gets Rs. 200 per month. Moreover, Rs. 500 per month is given to senior citizen beneficiaries whose age is above 80 years.", "005-listElement": "- **Vidhwa (Widow Pension)** \u2013 As per NSAP, each widow women in the age group of 40 to 79 years gets Rs. 200 per month while Rs. 500 per month is given to widow women above 80 years of age.", "006-listElement": "- **Viklang (Disabled Pension)** \u2013 For the differently-abled, the pension is fixed at Rs. 300 per month up to 79 years of age and Rs. 500 for 80 years and above.", "007-normal": "Along with this pension, Finance Minister had also announced an ex-gratia amount of Rs. 1,000 over the next 3 months and it will be given in two installments. This ex-gratia amount will be over and above the pension which is given on a monthly basis.", "008-normal": "Source / Reference Link: https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/wealth/personal-finance-news/elderly-differently-abled-widows-to-get-3-months-pension-in-advance/articleshow/74847650.cms"}}